HEADWORD: Anticlastic
<hw>An`ti*clas"tic</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧n`t⟦icr⟧*kl⟦acr⟧s"t⟦icr⟧k)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>anti-</ets> = Gr. <grk>kla^n</grk> to
break.]</ety> <def>Having opposite curvatures, that is, curved
longitudinally in one direction and transversely in the opposite
direction, as the surface of a saddle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anticlimax</ent>⟦br⟧
